# 🎓 EduCore — Tuition Institution Management System
### Full System Architecture & Feature Blueprint

---

## 📌 Overview

**EduCore** is a locally-installable, multi-role management platform designed for tuition institutes of any size. An institute owner downloads and installs the app, registers their institution, and the system auto-generates a full hierarchy of access for every stakeholder — from owner down to student.

---

## 🏗️ System Architecture at a Glance

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Platform / Super Admin] --> B[Institution Owner]
    B --> C[Workers / Managers]
    C --> D[Teachers]
    D --> E[Card Markers]
    D --> F[Students]
    E --> F
```

---

## 👥 Roles & Permissions

| Role | Description | Key Permissions |
|---|---|---|
| **Platform Admin** | The software vendor (you) | Manage licenses, view all institutions, push updates |
| **Institution Owner** | Registers & owns the institute | Full admin access, add/remove workers, view all reports |
| **Worker / Manager** | Operational staff assigned by Owner | Add teachers, students, card markers; manage classes, fees, schedules |
| **Teacher** | Subject educator | View own class students, schedule papers/tests, update weekly timetables, view student progress |
| **Card Marker** | Assigned per teacher | Mark attendance, collect class fees, report to teacher |
| **Student** | Registered learner | View own profile, classes, payments, marks, tutes/notes, progress analytics |

---

## 🖥️ Application Flow

### 1. Installation & Institution Registration
- Owner **downloads** the EduCore installer
- On first launch, a **Setup Wizard** runs:
  - Institute name, address, contact, logo
  - Owner personal information
  - License key activation (or free trial)
- After registration → Owner receives **Main Admin credentials** via registered email/SMS
- A local **SQLite database** is initialized for the institution

### 2. Owner Dashboard
- View institution-wide analytics
- Add / manage Workers
- Configure global settings (grade levels, subjects, fee structures, academic calendar)
- Generate and export reports (PDF/Excel)
- Manage subscription / license renewal

### 3. Worker / Manager Dashboard
- Add & manage Teachers, Students, Card Markers
- Create and manage **Classes** (assign teacher, subject, grade, room, schedule)
- Set fee structures per class
- Generate receipts and invoices
- Manage the academic calendar (holidays, exam periods)
- Handle student enrollment per class
- View all financial summaries

### 4. Teacher Dashboard
- View all assigned classes and enrolled students
- Check per-student: attendance %, fee payment status, marks, notes collected
- **Schedule Papers & Term Tests** (set date, subject, syllabus, max marks)
- **Update Weekly Timetable** (every Monday before 9 AM — system sends reminder)
- Upload notes/tutes for students to access
- View card marker reports

### 5. Card Marker Dashboard
- **Mark Daily Attendance** — per class session (Present / Absent / Late / Excused)
- **Collect Class Fees** — record payment, generate receipt, flag unpaid students
- View assigned teacher's class list
- Submit end-of-session reports to teacher

### 6. Student Portal
- Login with username & password
- View **My Classes** — enrolled classes, teacher info, schedule
- View **Payment History** — all fee receipts, outstanding amounts
- View **Academic Records** — marks per paper/term test, grade breakdown
- Download **Notes & Tutes** provided by teacher
- View **Attendance Record** — per class percentage
- **Progress Dashboard** — visual charts of marks trend, attendance trend, payment consistency

---

## 📦 Feature Modules

### 🏫 Institution Management
- Multi-branch support (one owner, many branches)
- Branch-level reporting
- Academic year / term configuration
- Subject and grade level master data

### 👨‍🎓 Student Management
- Student registration (name, DOB, contact, guardian details, photo)
- Unique Student ID generation
- Class enrollment (multi-class allowed)
- Student status tracking (Active / Inactive / Graduated)
- Student transfer between classes
- Student search and filter

### 👩‍🏫 Teacher Management
- Teacher profile (qualifications, subjects, contact)
- Class assignment management
- Weekly timetable module (Mon–Sun slots)
- Teaching hours summary per week/month

### 📋 Attendance Management
- Class-wise daily attendance by Card Marker
- Attendance percentage auto-calculated
- Low-attendance alerts (e.g., below 75%)
- Monthly attendance reports per student
- Bulk attendance marking with override

### 💰 Fee Management
- Class-wise fee structure
- Monthly, per-session, or annual fee modes
- Fee collection by Card Marker
- Payment receipts (printable PDF)
- Outstanding fee dashboard
- Payment reminders (SMS/email integration optional)
- Discount / scholarship management
- Financial summary reports

### 📝 Academic Records
- Paper / Term Test scheduling by Teacher
- Mark entry per student per exam
- Grade calculation with configurable grade bands
- Rank computation within class
- Cumulative GPA / average tracking
- Progress report card generation (PDF)

### 📅 Scheduling & Timetable
- Teacher weekly timetable editor (drag & drop or form-based)
- Class schedule viewer for students
- Academic calendar with holidays and exam periods
- Automated clash detection for rooms/teachers

### 📚 Learning Resources
- Teacher uploads notes / tutes (PDF, doc, images)
- Student downloads from their portal
- Resource tagged by class and subject
- Storage quota management

### 📊 Analytics & Reports
- **Student-level**: Attendance trend, marks trend, fee payment history
- **Class-level**: Average marks, attendance rates, fee collection rate
- **Institution-level**: Revenue summary, top-performing classes, enrollment growth
- Export: PDF, Excel, CSV
- Printable report cards for students

### 🔔 Notifications & Alerts
- In-app notification centre
- Teacher reminder: "Update timetable for next week" (every weekend)
- Student/Guardian: Low attendance warning, outstanding fee alert, upcoming exam reminder
- Optional: SMS gateway integration (Twilio / local provider)
- Optional: Email (SMTP)

### 🔐 Security & Access Control
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- All passwords hashed (bcrypt)
- Session management with auto-logout
- Audit log: who did what and when
- Data backup & restore (local + optional cloud)
- Owner can revoke any access instantly

---

## 🛠️ Recommended Tech Stack

### Option A — Desktop App (Recommended for "installable on PC")
| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| **Frontend UI** | Electron.js + React (or Svelte for lighter builds) |
| **Styling** | Tailwind CSS |
| **State Management** | Zustand / Redux Toolkit |
| **Database** | SQLite (via Better-SQLite3) — local, no server needed |
| **ORM** | Drizzle ORM or Sequelize |
| **PDF Generation** | Puppeteer / jsPDF |
| **Charts** | Recharts / Chart.js |
| **Auth** | JWT stored locally + bcrypt |
| **Packaging** | Electron Builder (generates `.exe` installer for Windows) |
| **Notifications** | Electron native notifications + optional Nodemailer |

### Option B — Web App (Hosted / Self-hostable)
| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| **Frontend** | Next.js 14 (App Router) |
| **Backend API** | Node.js + Express or Next.js API routes |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (hosted) or SQLite (self-hosted) |
| **Auth** | NextAuth.js |
| **File Storage** | Local filesystem or AWS S3 |
| **Deployment** | Docker container — owner runs it locally or on a small VPS |

> **Recommendation:** Go with **Option A (Electron)** for a true installable experience. You can later add a companion web portal for students/parents.

---

## 🗄️ Database Schema Overview

```
institutions          → id, name, address, logo, owner_id, license_key, created_at
users                 → id, institution_id, role, name, email, phone, password_hash, status
branches              → id, institution_id, name, location
academic_years        → id, institution_id, label, start_date, end_date
subjects              → id, institution_id, name, code
classes               → id, branch_id, subject_id, teacher_id, grade_level, room, fee_amount, fee_mode
enrollments           → id, class_id, student_id, enrolled_at, status
timetable_slots       → id, class_id, teacher_id, week_of, day, start_time, end_time
attendance_sessions   → id, class_id, date, card_marker_id
attendance_records    → id, session_id, student_id, status (present/absent/late/excused)
fee_collections       → id, enrollment_id, amount, paid_at, card_marker_id, receipt_no
exams                 → id, class_id, title, type (paper/term), scheduled_at, max_marks
exam_results          → id, exam_id, student_id, marks_obtained, grade
resources             → id, class_id, teacher_id, title, file_path, file_type, uploaded_at
notifications         → id, user_id, message, type, is_read, created_at
audit_logs            → id, user_id, action, entity, entity_id, timestamp
```

---

## 🔄 Key User Flows

### Student Login → Dashboard
```
Login → Verify credentials → Load enrolled classes →
Show: [Classes | Payments | Marks | Notes | Attendance | Progress]
```

### Card Marker → Mark Attendance
```
Login → Select Class → Select Date → Mark each student →
Submit → Session saved → Teacher notified
```

### Teacher → Schedule Exam
```
Login → My Classes → Select Class → Exams → New Exam →
Set Title / Type / Date / Max Marks → Publish → Students notified
```

### Worker → Enroll Student
```
Login → Students → Add/Search Student → Select Class(es) →
Confirm Enrollment → Student gets credentials
```

